abs550aer.comment: Optical thickness of atmospheric aerosols at wavelength 550 nanometers.
abs550aer.long_name: Ambient Aerosol Absorption Optical Thickness at 550nm

acabf.comment: Specific mass balance means the net rate at which ice is added per unit area at the land ice surface. Computed as the total surface mass balance on the land ice portion of the grid cell divided by land ice area in the grid cell. A negative value means loss of ice

acabfIs.comment: Specific mass balance means the net rate at which ice is added per unit area at the land ice surface. Computed as the total surface mass balance on the land ice portion of the grid cell divided by land ice area in the grid cell. A negative value means loss of ice
acabfIs.long_name: Ice Sheet Surface Mass Balance Flux

aerasymbnd.comment: The asymmetry factor is the angular integral of the aerosol scattering phase function weighted by the cosine of the angle with the incident radiation flux. The asymmetry coefficient is here an integral over all wavelength bands.
aerasymbnd.long_name: Aerosol Level Asymmetry Parameter for Each Band

aeroptbnd.comment: Optical thickness of atmospheric aerosols in wavelength bands.
aeroptbnd.long_name: Aerosol Level Absorption Optical Thickness for Each Band

aerssabnd.comment: The single scattering albedo is the fraction of radiation in an incident light beam scattered by the particles of an aerosol reference volume for a given wavelength. It is the ratio of the scattering and the extinction coefficients of the aerosol particles in the reference volume.
aerssabnd.long_name: Aerosol Level Single Scattering Albedo for Each Band

agesno.comment: Age of Snow (when computing the time-mean here, the time samples, weighted by the mass of snow on the land portion of the grid cell, are accumulated and then divided by the sum of the weights.  Reported as missing data in regions free of snow on land.

agessc.comment: Time elapsed since water was last in surface layer of the ocean.
agessc.long_name: Sea Water Age Since Surface Contact

airmass.comment: The mass of air in an atmospheric layer.
airmass.long_name: Vertically Integrated Mass Content of Air in Layer

albc.comment: Albedo of the vegetation: fraction of incoming solar radiation which is reflected before reaching the ground.

albdiffbnd.comment: The fraction of the surface diffuse downwelling shortwave radiation flux which is reflected. If the diffuse radiation is isotropic, this term is equivalent to the integral of surface bidirectional reflectance over all incident angles and over all outgoing angles in the hemisphere above the surface. Reported in spectral frequency bands.
albdiffbnd.long_name: Diffuse Surface Albedo for Each Band

albdirbnd.comment: The fraction of the surface direct downwelling shortwave radiation flux which is reflected. It is equivalent to the surface bidirectional reflectance at the incident angle of the incoming solar radiation and integrated over all outgoing angles in the hemisphere above the surface.  Reported in spectral frequency bands.
albdirbnd.long_name: Direct Surface Albedo for Each Band

albisccp.comment: ISCCP Mean Cloud Albedo. Time-means are weighted by the ISCCP Total Cloud Fraction {:cltisccp} - see  http://cfmip.metoffice.com/COSP.html

albsn.comment: Albedo of the snow-covered surface, averaged over the grid cell.

aoanh.comment: Fixed surface layer mixing ratio over 30o-50oN (0 ppbv), uniform fixed source (at all levels) everywhere else (source is unspecified but must be constant in space and time and documented). Note that the source could be 1yr/yr, so the tracer concentration provides mean age in years. For method using linearly increasing tracer include a method attribute: 'linearly increasing tracer'For method using uniform source (1yr/yr) include a method attribute: 'uniform source'

aod550volso4.comment: Aerosol optical depth at 550nm due to stratospheric volcanic aerosols
aod550volso4.long_name: Aerosol Optical Depth at 550nm Due to Stratospheric Volcanic Aerosols

arag.comment: Sum of particulate aragonite components (e.g. Phytoplankton, Detrital, etc.)

aragos.comment: sum of particulate aragonite components (e.g. Phytoplankton, Detrital, etc.)

areacella.comment: For atmospheres with more than 1 mesh (e.g., staggered grids), report areas that apply to surface vertical fluxes of energy.
areacella.long_name: Grid-Cell Area for Atmospheric Grid Variables

areacellg.comment: Area of the target grid (not the interpolated area of the source grid).
areacellg.long_name: Grid-Cell Area for Ice Sheet Variables

areacello.comment: Horizontal area of ocean grid cells

areacellr.comment: For river routing model, if grid differs from the atmospheric grid.
areacellr.long_name: Grid-Cell Area for River Model Variables

ares.comment: The 'aerodynamic_resistance' is the resistance to mixing through the boundary layer toward the surface by means of the dominant process, turbulent transport. Reference: Wesely, M. L., 1989,  doi:10.1016/0004-6981(89)90153-4.

bacc.comment: Sum of bacterial carbon component concentrations

baccos.comment: Sum of bacterial carbon component concentrations

baresoilFrac.comment: Percentage of entire grid cell  that is covered by bare soil.

basin.comment: A variable with the standard name of region contains strings which indicate geographical regions. These strings must be chosen from the standard region list.
basin.flag_meanings: global_land southern_ocean atlantic_ocean pacific_ocean arctic_ocean indian_ocean mediterranean_sea black_sea hudson_bay baltic_sea red_sea

bddtalk.comment: Net total of biological terms in time rate of change of alkalinity
bddtalk.long_name: Rate of Change of Alkalinity Due to Biological Activity

bddtdic.comment: Net total of biological terms in time rate of change of dissolved inorganic carbon
bddtdic.long_name: Rate of Change of Dissolved Inorganic Carbon Due to Biological Activity

bddtdife.comment: Net total of biological terms in time rate of change of dissolved inorganic iron
bddtdife.long_name: Rate of Change of Dissolved Inorganic Iron Due to Biological Activity

bddtdin.comment: Net total of biological terms in time rate of change of nitrogen nutrients (e.g. NO3+NH4)
bddtdin.long_name: Rate of Change of Nitrogen Nutrient Due to Biological Activity

bddtdip.comment: Net of biological terms in time rate of change of dissolved phosphate
bddtdip.long_name: Rate of Change of Dissolved Phosphorus Due to Biological Activity

bddtdisi.comment: Net of biological terms in time rate of change of dissolved inorganic silicon
bddtdisi.long_name: Rate of Change of Dissolved Inorganic Silicon Due to Biological Activity

bfe.comment: Sum of particulate organic iron component concentrations
bfe.long_name: Mole Concentration of Particulate Organic Matter Expressed as Iron in Sea Water

bfeos.comment: sum of particulate organic iron component concentrations
bfeos.long_name: Surface Mole Concentration of Particulate Organic Matter Expressed as Iron in Sea Water

bigthetao.comment: Sea water conservative temperature (this should be contributed only for models using conservative temperature as prognostic field)

bigthetaoga.comment: Diagnostic should be contributed only for models using conservative temperature as prognostic field.
bigthetaoga.long_name: Global Average Sea Water Conservative Temperature

bry.comment: Total family (the sum of all appropriate species in the model) ; list the species in the netCDF header, e.g. Bry = Br + BrO + HOBr + HBr + BrONO2 + BrCl Definition: Total inorganic bromine (e.g., HBr and inorganic bromine oxides and radicals (e.g., BrO, atomic bromine (Br), bromine nitrate (BrONO2)) resulting from degradation of bromine-containing organic source gases (halons, methyl bromide, VSLS), and natural inorganic bromine sources (e.g., volcanoes, sea salt, and other aerosols) add comment attribute with detailed description about how the model calculates these fields
bry.long_name: Total Inorganic Bromine Volume Mixing Ratio

bs550aer.comment: Aerosol  Backscatter at 550nm and 180 degrees, computed from extinction and lidar ratio

bsi.comment: Sum of particulate silica component concentrations
bsi.long_name: Mole Concentration of Particulate Organic Matter Expressed as Silicon in Sea Water

bsios.comment: sum of particulate silica component concentrations
bsios.long_name: Surface Mole Concentration of Particulate Organic Matter Expressed as Silicon in Sea Water

burntFractionAll.comment: Percentage of grid cell burned due to all fires including natural and anthropogenic fires and those associated with anthropogenic Land-use change
burntFractionAll.long_name: Percentage of Entire Grid Cell That Is Covered by Burnt Vegetation (All Classes)

c13Land.comment: Carbon-13 mass content per unit area in vegetation (any living plants e.g. trees, shrubs, grass), litter (dead plant material in or above the soil), soil, and forestry and agricultural products (e.g. paper, cardboard, furniture, timber for construction, biofuels and food for both humans and livestock).
c13Land.long_name: Mass of 13C in All Terrestrial Carbon Pools

c13Litter.comment: Carbon-13 mass content per unit area litter (dead plant material in or above the soil).

c13Soil.comment: Carbon-13 mass content per unit area in soil.

c13Veg.comment: Carbon-13 mass content per unit area in vegetation (any living plants e.g. trees, shrubs, grass).

c14Land.comment: Carbon-14 mass content per unit area in vegetation (any living plants e.g. trees, shrubs, grass), litter (dead plant material in or above the soil), soil, and forestry and agricultural products (e.g. paper, cardboard, furniture, timber for construction, biofuels and food for both humans and livestock).
c14Land.long_name: Mass of 14C in All Terrestrial Carbon Pools

c14Litter.comment: Carbon-14 mass content per unit area litter (dead plant material in or above the soil).

c14Soil.comment: Carbon-14 mass content per unit area in soil.

c14Veg.comment: Carbon-14 mass content per unit area in vegetation (any living plants e.g. trees, shrubs, grass).

c2h2.comment: Mole fraction is used in the construction mole_fraction_of_X_in_Y, where X is a material constituent of Y.

c2h6.comment: Mole fraction is used in the construction mole_fraction_of_X_in_Y, where X is a material constituent of Y.

c3PftFrac.comment: Percentage of entire grid cell  that is covered by C3 PFTs (including grass, crops, and trees).
c3PftFrac.long_name: Percentage Cover by C3 Plant Functional Type

c3h6.comment: Mole fraction is used in the construction mole_fraction_of_X_in_Y, where X is a material constituent of Y.

c3h8.comment: Mole fraction is used in the construction mole_fraction_of_X_in_Y, where X is a material constituent of Y.

c4PftFrac.comment: Percentage of entire grid cell  that is covered by C4 PFTs (including grass and crops).
c4PftFrac.long_name: Percentage Cover by C4 Plant Functional Type

cCwd.comment: Carbon mass per unit area in woody debris (dead organic matter composed of coarse wood.  It is distinct from litter)
cCwd.long_name: Carbon Mass in Coarse Woody Debris

cLand.comment: Report missing data over ocean grid cells. For fractional land report value averaged over the land fraction.
cLand.long_name: Total Carbon in All Terrestrial Carbon Pools

cLeaf.comment: Carbon mass per unit area in leaves.

cLitter.comment: 'Litter' is dead plant material in or above the soil. It is distinct from coarse wood debris. The precise distinction between 'fine' and 'coarse' is model dependent. 'Content' indicates a quantity per unit area. The sum of the quantities with standard names surface_litter_mass_content_of_carbon and subsurface_litter_mass_content_of_carbon has the standard name litter_mass_content_of_carbon.

cLitterAbove.comment: 'Litter' is dead plant material in or above the soil. It is distinct from coarse wood debris. The precise distinction between 'fine' and 'coarse' is model dependent. 'Surface litter' means the part of the litter resting above the soil surface. 'Content' indicates a quantity per unit area. The sum of the quantities with standard names surface_litter_mass_content_of_carbon and subsurface_litter_mass_content_of_carbon has the standard name litter_mass_content_of_carbon.

cLitterBelow.comment: 'Litter' is dead plant material in or above the soil. It is distinct from coarse wood debris. The precise distinction between 'fine' and 'coarse' is model dependent. 'subsurface litter' means the part of the litter mixed within the soil below the surface. 'Content' indicates a quantity per unit area. The sum of the quantities with standard names surface_litter_mass_content_of_carbon and subsurface_litter_mass_content_of_carbon has the standard name litter_mass_content_of_carbon.

cLitterCwd.comment: 'Content' indicates a quantity per unit area. 'Wood debris' means dead organic matter composed of coarse wood. It is distinct from fine litter. The precise distinction between 'fine' and 'coarse' is model dependent.
cLitterCwd.long_name: Carbon Mass in Coarse Woody Debris

cLitterGrass.comment: 'Litter' is dead plant material in or above the soil. It is distinct from coarse wood debris. The precise distinction between 'fine' and 'coarse' is model dependent. 'Content' indicates a quantity per unit area. The sum of the quantities with standard names surface_litter_mass_content_of_carbon and subsurface_litter_mass_content_of_carbon has the standard name litter_mass_content_of_carbon.
cLitterGrass.long_name: Carbon Mass in Litter on Grass Tiles

cLitterLut.comment: end of year values (not annual mean)
cLitterLut.long_name: Carbon  in Above and Below-Ground Litter Pools on Land-Use Tiles

cLitterShrub.comment: 'Litter' is dead plant material in or above the soil. It is distinct from coarse wood debris. The precise distinction between 'fine' and 'coarse' is model dependent. 'Content' indicates a quantity per unit area. The sum of the quantities with standard names surface_litter_mass_content_of_carbon and subsurface_litter_mass_content_of_carbon has the standard name litter_mass_content_of_carbon.
cLitterShrub.long_name: Carbon Mass in Litter on Shrub Tiles

cLitterSubSurf.comment: subsurface litter pool fed by root inputs.

cLitterSurf.comment: Surface or near-surface litter pool fed by leaf and above-ground litterfall

cLitterTree.comment: 'Litter' is dead plant material in or above the soil. It is distinct from coarse wood debris. The precise distinction between 'fine' and 'coarse' is model dependent. 'Content' indicates a quantity per unit area. The sum of the quantities with standard names surface_litter_mass_content_of_carbon and subsurface_litter_mass_content_of_carbon has the standard name litter_mass_content_of_carbon.
cLitterTree.long_name: Carbon Mass in Litter on Tree Tiles

cMisc.long_name: Carbon Mass in Other Living Compartments on Land

cOther.long_name: Carbon Mass in Vegetation Components Other than Leaves, Stems and Roots

cProduct.comment: Carbon mass per unit area in that has been removed from the environment through  land use change.
cProduct.long_name: Carbon Mass in Products of Land-Use Change

cProductLut.comment: Anthropogenic pools associated with land use tiles into which harvests and cleared carbon are deposited before release into atmosphere PLUS any remaining anthropogenic pools that may be associated with lands which were converted into land use tiles during reported period. Examples of products include paper, cardboard, timber for construction, and crop harvest for food or fuel. Does NOT include residue which is deposited into soil or litter; end of year values (not annual mean).
cProductLut.long_name: Wood and Agricultural Product Pool Carbon Associated with Land-Use Tiles

cRoot.comment: Carbon mass per unit area in roots, including fine and coarse roots.

cSoil.comment: Carbon mass in the full depth of the soil model.
cSoil.long_name: Carbon Mass in Model Soil Pool

cSoilAbove1m.comment: Report missing data over ocean grid cells. For fractional land report value averaged over the land fraction.
cSoilAbove1m.long_name: Carbon Mass in Soil Pool Above 1m Depth

cSoilFast.comment: Carbon mass per unit area in fast soil pool. Fast means a lifetime of less than 10 years for reference climate conditions (20th century) in the absence of water limitations.
cSoilFast.long_name: Carbon Mass in Fast Soil Pool

cSoilGrass.comment: 'Content' indicates a quantity per unit area. The 'soil content' of a quantity refers to the vertical integral from the surface down to the bottom of the soil model. For the content between specified levels in the soil, standard names including content_of_soil_layer are used.
cSoilGrass.long_name: Carbon Mass in Soil on Grass Tiles

cSoilLevels.comment: for models with vertically discretised soil carbon, report total soil carbon for each level
cSoilLevels.long_name: Carbon Mass in Each Model Soil Level (Summed over All Soil Carbon Pools in That Level)

cSoilLut.comment: end of year values (not annual mean)
cSoilLut.long_name: Carbon in Soil Pool on Land-Use Tiles

cSoilMedium.comment: Carbon mass per unit area in medium (rate) soil pool. Medium means a lifetime of more than than 10 years and less than 100 years for reference climate conditions (20th century) in the absence of water limitations.
cSoilMedium.long_name: Carbon Mass in Medium Soil Pool

cSoilPools.comment: For models with multiple soil carbon pools, report each pool here. If models also have vertical discretisation these should be aggregated
cSoilPools.long_name: Carbon Mass in Each Model Soil Pool (Summed over Vertical Levels)

cSoilShrub.comment: 'Content' indicates a quantity per unit area. The 'soil content' of a quantity refers to the vertical integral from the surface down to the bottom of the soil model. For the content between specified levels in the soil, standard names including content_of_soil_layer are used.
cSoilShrub.long_name: Carbon Mass in Soil on Shrub Tiles

cSoilSlow.comment: Carbon mass per unit area in slow soil pool. Slow means a lifetime of more than 100 years for reference climate (20th century) in the absence of water limitations.
cSoilSlow.long_name: Carbon Mass in Slow Soil Pool

cSoilTree.comment: 'Content' indicates a quantity per unit area. The 'soil content' of a quantity refers to the vertical integral from the surface down to the bottom of the soil model. For the content between specified levels in the soil, standard names including content_of_soil_layer are used.
cSoilTree.long_name: Carbon Mass in Soil on Tree Tiles

cTotFireLut.comment: Different from LMON this flux should include all fires occurring on the land use tile, including natural, man-made and deforestation fires
cTotFireLut.long_name: Total Carbon Loss from Natural and Managed Fire on Land-Use Tile, Including Deforestation Fires [kgC m-2 s-1]

cVeg.comment: Carbon mass per unit area in vegetation.

cVegGrass.comment: 'Content' indicates a quantity per unit area. 'Vegetation' means any plants e.g. trees, shrubs, grass. Plants are autotrophs i.e. 'producers' of biomass using carbon obtained from carbon dioxide.
cVegGrass.long_name: Carbon Mass in Vegetation on Grass Tiles

cVegLut.comment: end of year values (not annual mean)
cVegLut.long_name: Carbon in Vegetation on Land-Use Tiles

cVegShrub.comment: 'Content' indicates a quantity per unit area. 'Vegetation' means any plants e.g. trees, shrubs, grass. Plants are autotrophs i.e. 'producers' of biomass using carbon obtained from carbon dioxide.
cVegShrub.long_name: Carbon Mass in Vegetation on Shrub Tiles

cVegTree.comment: 'Content' indicates a quantity per unit area. 'Vegetation' means any plants e.g. trees, shrubs, grass. Plants are autotrophs i.e. 'producers' of biomass using carbon obtained from carbon dioxide.
cVegTree.long_name: Carbon Mass in Vegetation on Tree Tiles

cWood.comment: Carbon mass per unit area in wood, including sapwood and hardwood.

calc.comment: Sum of particulate calcite component concentrations (e.g. Phytoplankton, Detrital, etc.)

calcos.comment: sum of particulate calcite component concentrations (e.g. Phytoplankton, Detrital, etc.)

ccb.comment: Where convective cloud is present in the grid cell, the instantaneous cloud base altitude should be that of the bottom of the lowest level containing convective cloud. Missing data should be reported in the absence of convective cloud. The time mean should be calculated from these quantities averaging over occasions when convective cloud is present only, and should contain missing data for occasions when no convective cloud is present during the meaning period.
ccb.long_name: Air Pressure at Convective Cloud Base

ccldncl.comment: Droplets are liquid only.  Report concentration 'as seen from space' over convective liquid cloudy portion of grid cell.  This is the value from uppermost model layer with liquid cloud or, if available, it is better to sum over all liquid cloud tops, no matter where they occur, as long as they are seen from the top of the atmosphere. Weight by total liquid cloud top fraction of  (as seen from TOA) each time sample when computing monthly mean.
ccldncl.long_name: Cloud Droplet Number Concentration of Convective Cloud Tops

ccn.long_name: Cloud Condensation Nuclei Concentration at Liquid Cloud Top

cct.comment: Where convective cloud is present in the grid cell, the instantaneous cloud top altitude should be that of the top of the highest level containing convective cloud. Missing data should be reported in the absence of convective cloud. The time mean should be calculated from these quantities averaging over occasions when convective cloud is present only, and should contain missing data for occasions when no convective cloud is present during the meaning period.
cct.long_name: Air Pressure at Convective Cloud Top

cdnc.comment: Cloud Droplet Number Concentration in liquid water clouds.

cfadDbze94.comment: CFAD (Cloud Frequency Altitude Diagrams) are frequency distributions of radar  reflectivity (or lidar scattering ratio) as a function of altitude. The variable cfadDbze94 is defined as the simulated relative frequency of occurrence of radar reflectivity in sampling volumes defined by altitude bins. The radar is observing at a frequency of 94GHz.

cfadLidarsr532.comment: CFAD (Cloud Frequency Altitude Diagrams) are frequency distributions of radar  reflectivity (or lidar scattering ratio) as a function of altitude. The variable cfadLidarsr532 is defined as the simulated relative frequency of lidar scattering ratio in sampling volumes defined by altitude bins. The lidar is observing at a wavelength of 532nm.

cfc11.comment: Mole concentration means number of moles per unit volume, also called 'molarity', and is used in the construction 'mole_concentration_of_X_in_Y', where X is a material constituent of Y. A chemical or biological species denoted by X may be described by a single term such as 'nitrogen' or a phrase such as 'nox_expressed_as_nitrogen'. The chemical formula of CFC11 is CFCl3. The IUPAC name for CFC11 is trichloro-fluoro-methane.
cfc11.long_name: Mole Concentration of CFC11 in Sea Water

cfc113global.comment: Mole fraction is used in the construction mole_fraction_of_X_in_Y, where X is a material constituent of Y.  The chemical formula of CFC113 is CCl2FCClF2.  The IUPAC name for CFC113 is 1,1,2-trichloro-1,2,2-trifluoro-ethane.
cfc113global.long_name: Global Mean Mole Fraction of CFC113

cfc11global.comment: Mole fraction is used in the construction mole_fraction_of_X_in_Y, where X is a material constituent of Y.  The chemical formula of CFC11 is CFCl3.  The IUPAC name for CFC11 is trichloro-fluoro-methane.
cfc11global.long_name: Global Mean Mole Fraction of CFC11

cfc12.comment: Mole concentration means number of moles per unit volume, also called 'molarity', and is used in the construction 'mole_concentration_of_X_in_Y', where X is a material constituent of Y. A chemical or biological species denoted by X may be described by a single term such as 'nitrogen' or a phrase such as 'nox_expressed_as_nitrogen'. The chemical formula for CFC12 is CF2Cl2. The IUPAC name for CFC12 is dichloro-difluoro-methane.
cfc12.long_name: Mole Concentration of CFC12 in Sea Water

cfc12global.comment: Mole fraction is used in the construction mole_fraction_of_X_in_Y, where X is a material constituent of Y.  The chemical formula of CFC12 is CF2Cl2.  The IUPAC name for CFC12 is dichloro-difluoro-methane.
cfc12global.long_name: Global Mean Mole Fraction of CFC12

ch3coch3.comment: Mole fraction is used in the construction 'mole_fraction_of_X_in_Y', where X is a material constituent of Y. A chemical species denoted by X may be described by a single term such as 'nitrogen' or a phrase such as 'nox_expressed_as_nitrogen'. Acetone is an organic molecule with the chemical formula CH3CH3CO. The IUPAC name for acetone is propan-2-one. Acetone is a member of the group of organic compounds known as ketones. There are standard names for the ketone group as well as for some of the individual species.

ch4.comment: Mole fraction is used in the construction mole_fraction_of_X_in_Y, where X is a material constituent of Y.

ch4Clim.comment: Mole fraction is used in the construction mole_fraction_of_X_in_Y, where X is a material constituent of Y.

ch4global.comment: Global Mean Mole Fraction of CH4
ch4global.long_name: Global Mean Mole Fraction of CH4

ch4globalClim.comment: Global Mean Mole Fraction of CH4
ch4globalClim.long_name: Global Mean Mole Fraction of CH4

chepasoa.long_name: Total Net Production of Anthropogenic Secondary Organic Aerosol

chepsoa.comment: If model lumps secondary organic aerosol (SOA) emissions with primary organic aerosol (POA), then the sum of POA and SOA emissions is reported as OA emissions. Here, mass refers to the mass of primary organic matter, not mass of organic carbon alone.
chepsoa.long_name: Chemical Production of Dry Aerosol Secondary Organic Matter

chl.comment: Sum of chlorophyll from all phytoplankton group concentrations.  In most models this is equal to chldiat+chlmisc, that is the sum of Diatom Chlorophyll Mass Concentration and Other Phytoplankton Chlorophyll Mass Concentration
chl.long_name: Mass Concentration of Total Phytoplankton Expressed as Chlorophyll in Sea Water

chlcalc.comment: chlorophyll concentration from the calcite-producing phytoplankton component alone
chlcalc.long_name: Mass Concentration of Calcareous Phytoplankton Expressed as Chlorophyll in Sea Water

chlcalcos.comment: chlorophyll concentration from the calcite-producing phytoplankton component alone
chlcalcos.long_name: Surface Mass Concentration of Calcareous Phytoplankton Expressed as Chlorophyll in Sea Water

chldiat.comment: Chlorophyll from diatom phytoplankton component concentration alone
chldiat.long_name: Mass Concentration of Diatoms Expressed as Chlorophyll in Sea Water

chldiatos.comment: chlorophyll from diatom phytoplankton component concentration alone
chldiatos.long_name: Surface Mass Concentration of Diatoms Expressed as Chlorophyll in Sea Water

chldiaz.comment: Chlorophyll concentration from the diazotrophic phytoplankton component alone
chldiaz.long_name: Mass Concentration of Diazotrophs Expressed as Chlorophyll in Sea Water

chldiazos.comment: chlorophyll concentration from the diazotrophic phytoplankton component alone
chldiazos.long_name: Surface Mass Concentration of Diazotrophs Expressed as Chlorophyll in Sea Water

chlmisc.comment: Chlorophyll from additional phytoplankton component concentrations alone
chlmisc.long_name: Mass Concentration of Other Phytoplankton Expressed as Chlorophyll in Sea Water

chlmiscos.comment: chlorophyll from additional phytoplankton component concentrations alone
chlmiscos.long_name: Surface Mass Concentration of Other Phytoplankton Expressed as Chlorophyll in Sea Water

chlos.comment: Sum of chlorophyll from all phytoplankton group concentrations at the sea surface.  In most models this is equal to chldiat+chlmisc, that is the sum of 'Diatom Chlorophyll Mass Concentration' plus 'Other Phytoplankton Chlorophyll Mass Concentration'
chlos.long_name: Surface Mass Concentration of Total Phytoplankton Expressed as Chlorophyll in Sea Water

chlpico.comment: chlorophyll concentration from the picophytoplankton (<2 um) component alone
chlpico.long_name: Mass Concentration of Picophytoplankton Expressed as Chlorophyll in Sea Water

chlpicoos.comment: chlorophyll concentration from the picophytoplankton (<2 um) component alone
chlpicoos.long_name: Surface Mass Concentration of Picophytoplankton Expressed as Chlorophyll in Sea Water

ci.comment: Fraction of time that convection occurs in the grid cell.
ci.long_name: Fraction of Time Convection Occurs in Cell

cl.comment: Percentage cloud cover, including both large-scale and convective cloud.

clayfrac.comment: 'Volume fraction' is used in the construction volume_fraction_of_X_in_Y, where X is a material constituent of Y.

clcalipso.comment: Percentage cloud cover in CALIPSO standard atmospheric layers.

clcalipso2.comment: Clouds detected by CALIPSO but below the detectability threshold of CloudSat
clcalipso2.long_name: CALIPSO Cloud Cover Percentage Undetected by CloudSat (as Percentage of Area Covered)

clcalipsoice.comment: Percentage cloud cover in CALIPSO standard atmospheric layers.

clcalipsoliq.comment: Percentage liquid water ice cloud cover in CALIPSO standard atmospheric layers.

cldnci.comment: Concentration 'as seen from space' over ice-cloud portion of grid cell.  This is the value from uppermost model layer with ice cloud or, if available, it is the sum over all ice cloud tops, no matter where they occur, as long as they are seen from the top of the atmosphere. Weight by total ice cloud top fraction (as seen from TOA) of each time sample when computing monthly mean.
cldnci.long_name: Ice Crystal Number Concentration of Cloud Tops

cldncl.comment: Droplets are liquid only.  Report concentration 'as seen from space' over liquid cloudy portion of grid cell.  This is the value from uppermost model layer with liquid cloud or, if available, it is better to sum over all liquid cloud tops, no matter where they occur, as long as they are seen from the top of the atmosphere. Weight by total liquid cloud top fraction of  (as seen from TOA) each time sample when computing monthly mean.
cldncl.long_name: Cloud Droplet Number Concentration of Cloud Tops

cldnvi.comment: Droplets are liquid only.  Values are weighted by liquid cloud fraction in each layer when vertically integrating, and for monthly means the samples are weighted by total liquid cloud fraction (as seen from TOA).

clhcalipso.comment: Percentage cloud cover in layer centred on 220hPa
clhcalipso.long_name: CALIPSO High Level Cloud Area Percentage

cli.comment: Includes both large-scale and convective cloud. This is calculated as the mass of cloud ice in the grid cell divided by the mass of air (including the water in all phases) in the grid cell. It includes precipitating hydrometeors ONLY if the precipitating hydrometeors affect the calculation of radiative transfer in model.

clic.comment: Calculated as the mass of convective cloud ice  in the grid cell divided by the mass of air (including the water in all phases) in the grid cell.  This includes precipitating hydrometeors ONLY if the precipitating hydrometeors affect the calculation of radiative transfer in model.
clic.long_name: Mass Fraction of Convective Cloud Ice

climodis.comment: Total ice cloud area fraction (reported as a percentage) for the whole atmospheric column, as seen by the  Moderate Resolution Imaging Spectroradiometer (MODIS).

clis.comment: Calculated as the mass of stratiform cloud ice  in the grid cell divided by the mass of air (including the water in all phases) in the grid cell.  This includes precipitating hydrometeors ONLY if the precipitating hydrometeors affect the calculation of radiative transfer in model.
clis.long_name: Mass Fraction of Stratiform Cloud Ice

clisccp.comment: Percentage cloud cover in optical depth categories.

clivi.comment: mass of ice water in the column divided by the area of the column (not just the area of the cloudy portion of the column). Includes precipitating frozen hydrometeors ONLY if the precipitating hydrometeor affects the calculation of radiative transfer in model.

clivic.comment: calculate mass of convective ice water in the column divided by the area of the column (not just the area of the cloudy portion of the column). This includes precipitating frozen hydrometeors ONLY if the precipitating hydrometeors affect the calculation of radiative transfer in model.

cllcalipso.comment: Percentage cloud cover in layer centred on 840hPa
cllcalipso.long_name: CALIPSO Low Level Cloud Cover Percentage

clmcalipso.comment: Percentage cloud cover in layer centred on 560hPa
clmcalipso.long_name: CALIPSO Mid Level Cloud Cover Percentage

clmisr.comment: Cloud percentage in spectral bands and layers as observed by the Multi-angle Imaging SpectroRadiometer (MISR) instrument. The first layer in each profile is reserved for a retrieval error flag.
clmisr.long_name: Percentage Cloud Cover as Calculated by the MISR Simulator (Including Error Flag)

cls.comment: Cloud area fraction (reported as a percentage) for the whole atmospheric column due to stratiform clouds, as seen from the surface or the top of the atmosphere. Includes both large-scale and convective cloud.

clt.comment: Total cloud area fraction (reported as a percentage) for the whole atmospheric column, as seen from the surface or the top of the atmosphere. Includes both large-scale and convective cloud.

cltc.comment: Convective cloud area fraction (reported as a percentage) for the whole atmospheric column, as seen from the surface or the top of the atmosphere. Includes only convective cloud.

cltcalipso.comment: Total cloud area fraction (reported as a percentage) for the whole atmospheric column, as seen by the  Cloud-Aerosol Lidar and Infrared Pathfinder Satellite Observation (CALIPSO) instrument. Includes both large-scale and convective cloud.

cltisccp.comment: Total cloud area fraction (reported as a percentage) for the whole atmospheric column, as seen by the International Satellite Cloud Climatology Project (ISCCP) analysis. Includes both large-scale and convective cloud.  (MODIS). Includes both large-scale and convective cloud.

cltmodis.comment: Total cloud area fraction (reported as a percentage) for the whole atmospheric column, as seen by the  Moderate Resolution Imaging Spectroradiometer (MODIS). Includes both large-scale and convective cloud.

clw.comment: Includes both large-scale and convective cloud. Calculate as the mass of cloud liquid water in the grid cell divided by the mass of air (including the water in all phases) in the grid cells. Precipitating hydrometeors are included ONLY if the precipitating hydrometeors affect the calculation of radiative transfer in model.
clw.long_name: Mass Fraction of Cloud Liquid Water

clwc.comment: Calculated as the mass of convective cloud liquid water in the grid cell divided by the mass of air (including the water in all phases) in the grid cell.  This includes precipitating hydrometeors ONLY if the precipitating hydrometeors affect the calculation of radiative transfer in model.
clwc.long_name: Mass Fraction of Convective Cloud Liquid Water

clwmodis.comment: Mass of cloud liquid water, as seen by the  Moderate Resolution Imaging Spectroradiometer (MODIS). Includes both large-scale and convective cloud.

clws.comment: Calculated as the mass of stratiform cloud liquid water in the grid cell divided by the mass of air (including the water in all phases) in the grid cell.  This includes precipitating hydrometeors ONLY if the precipitating hydrometeors affect the calculation of radiative transfer in model.
clws.long_name: Mass Fraction of Stratiform Cloud Liquid Water

clwvi.comment: Mass of condensed (liquid + ice) water in the column divided by the area of the column (not just the area of the cloudy portion of the column). Includes precipitating hydrometeors ONLY if the precipitating hydrometeors affect the calculation of radiative transfer in model.

clwvic.comment: calculate mass of convective condensed (liquid + ice) water in the column divided by the area of the column (not just the area of the cloudy portion of the column). This includes precipitating hydrometeors ONLY if the precipitating hydrometeors affect the calculation of radiative transfer in model.

cly.comment: Total family (the sum of all appropriate species in the model) ; list the species in the netCDF header, e.g. Cly = HCl + ClONO2 + HOCl + ClO + Cl + 2*Cl2O2 +2Cl2 + OClO + BrCl Definition: Total inorganic stratospheric chlorine (e.g., HCl, ClO) resulting from degradation of chlorine-containing source gases (CFCs, HCFCs, VSLS), and natural inorganic chlorine sources (e.g., sea salt and other aerosols) add comment attribute with detailed description about how the model calculates these fields
cly.long_name: Total Inorganic Chlorine Volume Mixing Ratio

cnc.comment: Percentage of area covered by vegetation.

co.comment: Mole fraction is used in the construction mole_fraction_of_X_in_Y, where X is a material constituent of Y.

co2.comment: Mole fraction is used in the construction mole_fraction_of_X_in_Y, where X is a material constituent of Y.

co23D.comment: report 3D field of model simulated atmospheric CO2 mass mixing ration on model levels

co2Clim.comment: Mole fraction is used in the construction mole_fraction_of_X_in_Y, where X is a material constituent of Y.

co2mass.comment: Total atmospheric mass of Carbon Dioxide

co2massClim.comment: Total atmospheric mass of Carbon Dioxide

co2s.comment: As co2, but only at the surface

co3.comment: Mole concentration (number of moles per unit volume: molarity) of the carbonate anion (CO3).

co3abio.comment: Mole concentration (number of moles per unit volume: molarity) of the abiotic-analogue carbonate anion (CO3). An abiotic analogue is used to simulate the effect on a modelled variable when biological effects on ocean carbon concentration and alkalinity are ignored.

co3abioos.comment: Near surface mole concentration (number of moles per unit volume: molarity) of the abiotic-analogue carbonate anion (CO3). An abiotic analogue is used to simulate the effect on a modelled variable when biological effects on ocean carbon concentration and alkalinity are ignored.

co3nat.comment: Surface mole concentration (number of moles per unit volume: molarity) of the natural-analogue carbonate anion (CO3). A natural analogue is used to simulate the effect on a modelled variable of imposing preindustrial atmospheric carbon dioxide concentrations, even when the model as a whole may be subjected to varying forcings.

co3natos.comment: Near surface mole concentration (number of moles per unit volume: molarity) of the natural-analogue carbonate anion (CO3). A natural analogue is used to simulate the effect on a modelled variable of imposing preindustrial atmospheric carbon dioxide concentrations, even when the model as a whole may be subjected to varying forcings.

co3os.comment: Near surface mole concentration (number of moles per unit volume: molarity) of the carbonate anion (CO3).

co3satarag.comment: Mole concentration (number of moles per unit volume: molarity) of the carbonate anion (CO3) for sea water in equilibrium with pure Aragonite. Aragonite  (CaCO3) is a mineral that is a polymorph of calcium carbonate.
co3satarag.long_name: Mole Concentration of Carbonate Ion in Equilibrium with Pure Aragonite in Sea Water

co3sataragos.comment: Near surface mole concentration (number of moles per unit volume: molarity) of the carbonate anion (CO3) for sea water in equilibrium with pure Aragonite. Aragonite  (CaCO3) is a mineral that is a polymorph of calcium carbonate.
co3sataragos.long_name: Surface Mole Concentration of Carbonate Ion in Equilibrium with Pure Aragonite in Sea Water

co3satcalc.comment: Mole concentration (number of moles per unit volume: molarity) of the carbonate anion (CO3) for sea water in equilibrium with pure calcite. Aragonite  (CaCO3) is a mineral that is a polymorph of calcium carbonate.
co3satcalc.long_name: Mole Concentration of Carbonate Ion in Equilibrium with Pure Calcite in Sea Water

co3satcalcos.comment: Near surface mole concentration (number of moles per unit volume: molarity) of the carbonate anion (CO3) for sea water in equilibrium with pure calcite. Aragonite  (CaCO3) is a mineral that is a polymorph of calcium carbonate.
co3satcalcos.long_name: Surface Mole Concentration of Carbonate Ion in Equilibrium with Pure Calcite in Sea Water

cod.comment: The optical thickness is the integral along the path of radiation of a volume scattering/absorption/attenuation coefficient. The radiative flux is reduced by a factor exp(-optical_thickness) on traversing the path. A coordinate variable of radiation_wavelength or radiation_frequency can be specified to indicate that the optical thickness applies at specific wavelengths or frequencies. The atmosphere optical thickness applies to radiation passing through the entire atmosphere. 'Cloud' means the component of extinction owing to the presence of liquid or ice water particles. The specification of a physical process by the phrase due_to_process means that the quantity named is a  single term in a sum of terms which together compose the general quantity named by omitting the phrase.

conccmcn.comment: includes all particles with diameter larger than 1 micron

conccn.comment: 'Number concentration' means the number of particles or other specified objects per unit volume. 'Aerosol' means the system of suspended liquid or solid particles in air (except cloud droplets) and their carrier gas, the air itself. 'Ambient_aerosol' means that the aerosol is measured or modelled at the ambient state of pressure, temperature and relative humidity that exists in its immediate environment. 'Ambient aerosol particles' are aerosol particles that have taken up ambient water through hygroscopic growth. The extent of hygroscopic growth depends on the relative humidity and the composition of the particles.

concdust.comment: Mass concentration means mass per unit volume and is used in the construction mass_concentration_of_X_in_Y, where X is a material constituent of Y. A chemical species denoted by X may be described by a single term such as 'nitrogen' or a phrase such as 'nox_expressed_as_nitrogen'. 'Aerosol' means the system of suspended liquid or solid particles in air (except cloud droplets) and their carrier gas, the air itself. Aerosol particles take up ambient water (a process known as hygroscopic growth) depending on the relative humidity and the composition of the particles. 'Dry aerosol particles' means aerosol particles without any water uptake.

concnmcn.comment: includes all particles with diameter smaller than 3 nm
concnmcn.long_name: Number Concentration of Nucleation Mode Aerosol

cropFrac.comment: Percentage of entire grid cell  that is covered by crop.

cropFracC3.comment: Percentage of entire grid cell covered by C3 crops

cropFracC4.comment: Percentage of entire grid cell covered by C4 crops

cw.comment: 'Amount' means mass per unit area. 'Water' means water in all phases, including frozen i.e. ice and snow. 'Canopy' means the plant or vegetation canopy. The canopy water is the water on the canopy.

darag.comment: Rate of change of Aragonite carbon mole concentration  due to dissolution

dcalc.comment: Rate of change of Calcite carbon mole concentration  due to dissolution

dcw.comment: The phrase 'change_over_time_in_X' means change in a quantity X over a time-interval, which should be defined by the bounds of the time coordinate. 'Canopy' means the plant or vegetation canopy. Canopy water is the water on the canopy. 'Water' means water in all phases, including frozen, i.e. ice and snow. 'Amount' means mass per unit area.

demc.comment: This is the in-cloud emissivity obtained by considering only the cloudy portion of the grid cell.

dems.comment: This is the in-cloud emissivity obtained by considering only the cloudy portion of the grid cell.

depdust.comment: Fdry mass deposition rate of dust

deptho.comment: Ocean bathymetry.   Reported here is the sea floor depth for present day relative to z=0 geoid. Reported as missing for land grid cells.

detoc.comment: Sum of detrital organic carbon component concentrations

detocos.comment: sum of detrital organic carbon component concentrations

dfe.comment: Dissolved iron in sea water,  including both Fe2+ and Fe3+ ions (but not particulate detrital iron)

dfeos.comment: dissolved iron in sea water is meant to include both Fe2+ and Fe3+ ions (but not, e.g., particulate detrital iron)

dgw.comment: Groundwater is subsurface water below the depth of the water table.

diabdrag.comment: Other sub-grid scale/numerical zonal drag excluding that already provided for the parameterized orographic and non-orographic gravity waves. This would be used to calculate the total 'diabatic drag'. Contributions to this additional drag such Rayleigh friction and diffusion that can be calculated from the monthly mean wind fields should not be included, but details (e.g. coefficients) of the friction and/or diffusion used in the model should be provided separately.
diabdrag.long_name: Tendency of Eastward Wind from Numerical Artefacts

difmxybo.comment: Lateral biharmonic viscosity applied to the momentum equations.

difmxybo2d.comment: Lateral biharmonic viscosity applied to the momentum equations.

difmxylo.comment: Lateral Laplacian viscosity applied to the momentum equations.

difmxylo2d.comment: Lateral Laplacian viscosity applied to the momentum equations.

diftrbbo.comment: Parameterized mesoscale eddy advection occurs on a spatial scale of many tens of kilometres and an evolutionary time of weeks(sometimes called bolus advection). Reference: James C. McWilliams 2016, Submesoscale currents in the ocean, Proceedings of the Royal Society A: Mathematical, Physical and Engineering Sciences, volume 472, issue 2189. DOI: 10.1098/rspa.2016.0117.

diftrbbo2d.comment: Parameterized mesoscale eddy advection occurs on a spatial scale of many tens of kilometres and an evolutionary time of weeks(sometimes called bolus advection). Reference: James C. McWilliams 2016, Submesoscale currents in the ocean, Proceedings of the Royal Society A: Mathematical, Physical and Engineering Sciences, volume 472, issue 2189. DOI: 10.1098/rspa.2016.0117.

diftrblo.comment: Ocean tracer diffusivity associated with parameterized eddy-induced advective transport. Sometimes this diffusivity is called the 'thickness' diffusivity. For CMIP5, this diagnostic was called 'ocean tracer bolus laplacian diffusivity'.  The CMIP6 name is physically more relevant.
diftrblo.long_name: Ocean Tracer Diffusivity Due to Parameterized Mesoscale Advection

diftrblo2d.comment: Ocean tracer diffusivity associated with parameterized eddy-induced advective transport. Sometimes this diffusivity is called the 'thickness' diffusivity. For CMIP5, this diagnostic was called 'ocean tracer bolus laplacian diffusivity'.  The CMIP6 name is physically more relevant.
diftrblo2d.long_name: Ocean Tracer Diffusivity Due to Parameterized Mesoscale Advection

diftrebo.comment: Epineutral diffusivity means a lateral diffusivity along a either a neutral or isopycnal density surface due to motion which is not resolved on the grid scale of an ocean model. The type of density surface is dependent on the model formulation.

diftrebo2d.comment: Epineutral diffusivity means a lateral diffusivity along a either a neutral or isopycnal density surface due to motion which is not resolved on the grid scale of an ocean model. The type of density surface is dependent on the model formulation.

diftrelo.comment: Ocean tracer diffusivity associated with parameterized eddy-induced diffusive transport oriented along neutral or isopycnal directions. Sometimes this diffusivity is called the neutral diffusivity or isopycnal diffusivity or Redi diffusivity.

diftrelo2d.comment: Ocean tracer diffusivity associated with parameterized eddy-induced diffusive transport oriented along neutral or isopycnal directions. Sometimes this diffusivity is called the neutral diffusivity or isopycnal diffusivity or Redi diffusivity.

diftrxybo.comment: Diffusivity is also sometimes known as the coefficient of diffusion. Diffusion occurs as a result of a gradient in the spatial distribution of mass concentration, temperature or momentum.  The diffusivity may be very different in the vertical and horizontal directions. 'xy diffusivity' means the lateral along_coordinate component of diffusivity due to motion which is not resolved on the grid scale of the model.  xy diffusivities are used in some ocean models to counteract the numerical instabilities inherent in certain implementations of rotated neutral diffusion. 'biharmonic diffusivity' means diffusivity for use with a biharmonic diffusion operator.

diftrxybo2d.comment: Diffusivity is also sometimes known as the coefficient of diffusion. Diffusion occurs as a result of a gradient in the spatial distribution of mass concentration, temperature or momentum.  The diffusivity may be very different in the vertical and horizontal directions. 'xy diffusivity' means the lateral along_coordinate component of diffusivity due to motion which is not resolved on the grid scale of the model.  xy diffusivities are used in some ocean models to counteract the numerical instabilities inherent in certain implementations of rotated neutral diffusion. 'biharmonic diffusivity' means diffusivity for use with a biharmonic diffusion operator.

Diffusion occurs as a result of a gradient in the spatial distribution of mass concentration, temperature or momentum.  The diffusivity may be very different in the vertical and horizontal directions. 'xy diffusivity' means the lateral along_coordinate component of diffusivity due to motion which is not resolved on the grid scale of the model.  xy diffusivities are used in some ocean models to counteract the numerical instabilities inherent in certain implementations of rotated neutral diffusion. diftrxylo2d.comment: Diffusivity is also sometimes known as the coefficient of diffusion. Diffusion occurs as a result of a gradient in the spatial distribution of mass concentration, temperature or momentum.  The diffusivity may be very different in the vertical and horizontal directions. 'xy diffusivity' means the lateral along_coordinate component of diffusivity due to motion which is not resolved on the grid scale of the model.  xy diffusivities are used in some ocean models to counteract the numerical instabilities inherent in certain implementations of rotated neutral diffusion. difvho.comment: Vertical/dianeutral diffusivity applied to prognostic temperature field.

difvmbo.comment: Vertical/dianeutral diffusivity applied to momentum due to the background (i.e. caused by a time invariant imposed field which may be either constant over the globe or spatially varying, depending on the ocean model used).
difvmbo.long_name: Ocean Vertical Momentum Diffusivity Due to Background

difvmfdo.comment: Vertical/dianeutral diffusivity applied to momentum due to form drag (i.e. resulting from a model scheme representing  mesoscale eddy-induced form drag).
difvmfdo.long_name: Ocean Vertical Momentum Diffusivity Due to Form Drag

difvmto.comment: Diffusivity is also sometimes known as the coefficient of diffusion. Diffusion occurs as a result of a gradient in the spatial distribution of mass concentration, temperature or momentum.  The diffusivity may be very different in the vertical and horizontal directions. The construction vertical_X_diffusivity means the vertical component of the diffusivity of X due to motion which is not resolved on the grid scale of the model. 'Due to tides' means due to all astronomical gravity changes which manifest as tides. No distinction is made between different tidal components. The specification of a physical process by the phrase due_to_process means that the quantity named is a  single term in a sum of terms which together compose the general quantity  named by omitting the phrase.
difvmto.long_name: Ocean Vertical Momentum Diffusivity Due to Tides

difvso.comment: Vertical/dianeutral diffusivity applied to prognostic salinity field.

difvtrbo.comment: Vertical/dianeutral diffusivity applied to tracers due to the background (i.e. caused by a time invariant imposed field which may be either constant over the globe or spatially varying, depending on the ocean model used).
difvtrbo.long_name: Ocean Vertical Tracer Diffusivity Due to Background

difvtrto.comment: Vertical/dianeutral diffusivity applied to tracers due to tides (i.e. caused by astronomical gravity changes which manifest as tides).
difvtrto.long_name: Ocean Vertical Tracer Diffusivity Due to Tides

dispkevfo.comment: Friction, leading to the dissipation of kinetic energy, arises in ocean models as a result of the viscosity of sea water.  Generally, the  lateral (xy) viscosity is given a large value to maintain the numerical stability of the model.  In contrast, the vertical viscosity is usually much smaller. The specification of a physical process by the phrase due_to_process means that the quantity named is a  single term in a sum of terms which together compose the general quantity  named by omitting the phrase.
dispkevfo.long_name: Ocean Kinetic Energy Dissipation per Unit Area Due to Vertical Friction

dispkexyfo.comment: Depth integrated impacts on kinetic energy arising from lateral frictional dissipation associated with Laplacian and/or biharmonic viscosity. For CMIP5, this diagnostic was 3d, whereas the CMIP6 depth integrated diagnostic is sufficient for many purposes and reduces archive requirements.
dispkexyfo.long_name: Ocean Kinetic Energy Dissipation per Unit Area Due to XY Friction

dispkexyfo2d.comment: Depth integrated impacts on kinetic energy arising from lateral frictional dissipation associated with Laplacian and/or biharmonic viscosity. For CMIP5, this diagnostic was 3d, whereas the CMIP6 depth integrated diagnostic is sufficient for many purposes and reduces archive requirements.
dispkexyfo2d.long_name: Ocean Kinetic Energy Dissipation per Unit Area Due to XY Friction

dissi13cos.comment: Near surface dissolved inorganic carbon-13 (CO3+HCO3+H2CO3) concentration

dissi14cabioos.long_name: Surface Abiotic Dissolved Inorganic Carbon-14 Concentration

dissicabioos.long_name: Surface Abiotic Dissolved Inorganic Carbon Concentration

dissicnat.comment: Dissolved inorganic carbon (CO3+HCO3+H2CO3) concentration at preindustrial atmospheric xCO2

dissicnatos.comment: Dissolved inorganic carbon (CO3+HCO3+H2CO3) concentration at preindustrial atmospheric xCO2
dissicnatos.long_name: Surface Natural Dissolved Inorganic Carbon Concentration

dissoc.comment: Sum of dissolved carbon component concentrations explicitly represented (i.e. not ~40 uM refractory unless explicit)

dissocos.comment: Sum of dissolved carbon component concentrations explicitly represented (i.e. not ~40 uM refractory unless explicit)

dmc.comment: The net mass flux  represents the difference between the updraft and downdraft components.   This is calculated as the convective mass flux divided by the area of the whole grid cell (not just the area of the cloud).

dmlt.comment: Depth from surface to the zero degree isotherm. Above this isotherm T > 0o, and below this line T < 0o. Missing if surface is frozen or if soil is unfrozen at all depths.

dms.comment: Mole fraction is used in the construction mole_fraction_of_X_in_Y, where X is a material constituent of Y.

dmso.comment: Mole concentration of dimethyl sulphide in water
dmso.long_name: Mole Concentration of Dimethyl Sulphide in Sea Water

dmsos.comment: Mole concentration of dimethyl sulphide in water in the near surface layer
dmsos.long_name: Surface Mole Concentration of Dimethyl Sulphide in Sea Water

dpco2.comment: Difference in partial pressure of carbon dioxide between sea water and air.  The partial pressure of a dissolved gas in sea water is the partial pressure in air with which it would be in equilibrium.

dpco2abio.comment: Difference in partial pressure of abiotic-analogue carbon dioxide between sea water and air.  The partial pressure of a dissolved gas in sea water is the partial pressure in air with which it would be in equilibrium. An abiotic analogue is used to simulate the effect on a modelled variable when biological effects on ocean carbon concentration and alkalinity are ignored.

dpco2nat.comment: Difference in partial pressure of natural-analogue carbon dioxide between sea water and air.  The partial pressure of a dissolved gas in sea water is the partial pressure in air with which it would be in equilibrium.  A natural analogue is used to simulate the effect on a modelled variable of imposing preindustrial atmospheric carbon dioxide concentrations, even when the model as a whole may be subjected to varying forcings.

dpo2.comment: The partial pressure of a dissolved gas in sea water is the partial pressure in air with which it would be in equilibrium.  The partial pressure of a gaseous constituent of air is the pressure which it alone would exert with unchanged temperature and number of moles per unit volume.  The surface called 'surface' means the lower boundary of the atmosphere.

drivw.comment: Change over time of the mass of water per unit area in the fluvial system (stream and floodplain).

drybc.comment: Dry deposition includes gravitational settling and turbulent deposition.
drybc.long_name: Dry Deposition Rate of Black Carbon Aerosol Mass

drydust.comment: Dry deposition includes gravitational settling and turbulent deposition.

drynh3.comment: Dry Deposition includes gravitational settling and turbulent deposition

drynh4.comment: Dry Deposition includes gravitational settling and turbulent deposition

drynoy.comment: NOy is the sum of all simulated oxidized nitrogen species out of NO, NO2, HNO3, HNO4, NO3 aerosol, NO3(radical), N2O5, PAN, other organic nitrates. Dry deposition includes gravitational settling and turbulent deposition.

dryo3.comment: Dry Deposition includes gravitational settling and turbulent deposition.

dryoa.comment: Tendency of atmosphere mass content of organic dry aerosol due to dry deposition: This is the sum of dry deposition of primary organic aerosol (POA) and dry deposition of secondary organic aerosol (SOA). Here, mass refers to the mass of organic matter, not mass of organic carbon alone.  We recommend a scale factor of POM=1.4*OC, unless your model has more detailed info available. Was called dry_pom in old ACCMIP Excel table. Dry deposition includes gravitational settling and turbulent deposition.
dryoa.long_name: Dry Deposition Rate of Dry Aerosol Total Organic Matter

dryso2.comment: Dry Deposition includes gravitational settling and turbulent deposition

dryso4.comment: Dry Deposition includes gravitational settling and turbulent deposition

dryss.comment: Dry deposition includes gravitational settling and turbulent deposition.
dryss.long_name: Dry Deposition Rate of Sea-Salt Aerosol

dslw.comment: The phrase 'change_over_time_in_X' means change in a quantity X over a time-interval, which should be defined by the bounds of the time coordinate. 'Content' indicates a quantity per unit area. The mass content of water in soil refers to the vertical integral from the surface down to the bottom of the soil model. For the content between specified levels in the soil, standard names including 'content_of_soil_layer' are used. 'Water' means water in all phases.

dsn.comment: Change in time of the mass per unit area of ice in glaciers, ice caps, ice sheets and shelves, river and lake ice, any other ice on a land surface, such as frozen flood water, and snow lying on such ice or on the land surface.

dsw.comment: The phrase 'land_water_amount', often known as 'Terrestrial Water Storage', includes: surface liquid water (water in rivers, wetlands, lakes, reservoirs, rainfall intercepted by the canopy); surface ice and snow (glaciers, ice caps, grounded ice sheets not displacing sea water, river and lake ice, other surface ice such as frozen flood water, snow lying on the surface and intercepted by the canopy); subsurface water (liquid and frozen soil water, groundwater).

dtauc.comment: This is the in-cloud optical depth obtained by considering only the cloudy portion of the grid cell

dtaus.comment: This is the in-cloud optical depth obtained by considering only the cloudy portion of the grid cell.

dtes.comment: Change in heat storage over the soil layer and the vegetation for which the energy balance is calculated, accumulated over the sampling time interval.

dtesn.comment: Change in cold content over the snow layer for which the energy balance is calculated, accumulated over the sampling time interval. This should also include the energy contained in the liquid water in the snow pack.
dtesn.long_name: Change in Snow and Ice Cold Content

ec.comment: Evaporation flux from water in all phases on the vegetation canopy.

ec550aer.comment: Aerosol volume extinction coefficient at 550nm wavelength.

edt.comment: Vertical diffusion coefficient for temperature due to parametrised eddies

emiaco.long_name: Total Emission Rate of Anthropogenic CO

emianox.comment: Store flux as Nitrogen. Anthropogenic fraction. NOx=NO+NO2, Includes agricultural waste burning but no other biomass burning. Integrate 3D emission field vertically to 2d field.
emianox.long_name: Total Emission Rate of Anthropogenic NOx

emiaoa.long_name: Total Emission Rate of Anthropogenic Organic Aerosol

emibc.comment: Integrate 3D emission field vertically to 2d field.
emibc.long_name: Total Emission Rate of Black Carbon Aerosol Mass

emibvoc.comment: Integrate 3D emission field vertically to 2d field._If_ fixed molecular weight of NMVOC is not available in model, please provide in units of kilomole m-2 s-1 (i.e. kg m-2 s-1 as if model NMVOC had molecular weight of 1) and add a comment to your file.
emibvoc.long_name: Total Emission Rate of Biogenic NMVOC

emico.comment: Integrate 3D emission field vertically to 2d field.

emidms.comment: Integrate 3D emission field vertically to 2d field.

emidust.comment: Integrate 3D emission field vertically to 2d field.

emiisop.comment: Integrate 3D emission field vertically to 2d field

emilnox.comment: Integrate the NOx production for lightning over model layer. proposed name: tendency_of_atmosphere_mass_content_of_nox_from_lightning

eminh3.comment: Integrate 3D emission field vertically to 2d field.

eminox.comment: NOx=NO+NO2. Integrate 3D emission field vertically to 2d field.

emioa.comment: This is the sum of total emission of primary organic aerosol (POA) and total production of secondary organic aerosol (SOA) (emipoa+chepsoa). Here, mass refers to the mass of organic matter, not mass of organic carbon alone. We recommend a scale factor of POM=1.4*OC, unless your model has more detailed info available.  Integrate 3D chemical production and emission field vertically to 2d field.
emioa.long_name: Primary Emission and Chemical Production of Dry Aerosol Organic Matter

emiso2.comment: Integrate 3D emission field vertically to 2d field.

emiso4.comment: Direct primary emission does not include secondary sulfate production. Integrate 3D emission field vertically to 2d field.
emiso4.long_name: Total Direct Emission Rate of SO4

emiss.comment: Integrate 3D emission field vertically to 2d field.
emiss.long_name: Total Emission Rate of Sea-Salt Aerosol

emivoc.comment: Integrate 3D emission field vertically to 2d field. _If_ fixed molecular weight of NMVOC is not available in model, please provide in units of kilomole m-2 s-1 (i.e. kg m-2 s-1 as if model NMVOC had molecular weight of 1) and add a comment to your file.

eow.comment: Evaporation (conversion of liquid or solid into vapor) from open water.

eparag100.comment: The phrase 'expressed_as' is used in the construction A_expressed_as_B, where B is a chemical constituent of A. It means that the quantity indicated by the standard name is calculated solely with respect to the B contained in A, neglecting all other chemical constituents of A. In accordance with common usage in geophysical disciplines, 'flux' implies per unit area, called 'flux density' in physics.   'Sinking' is the gravitational settling of particulate matter suspended in a liquid. A sinking flux is positive downwards and is calculated relative to the movement of the surrounding fluid. Aragonite is a mineral that is a polymorph of calcium carbonate. The chemical formula of aragonite is CaCO3. Standard names also exist for calcite, another polymorph of calcium carbonate.

epfy.comment: Transformed Eulerian Mean Diagnostics Meridional component Fy of Eliassen-Palm (EP) flux (Fy, Fz) derived from 6hr or higher frequency fields (use daily fields or 12 hr fields if the 6 hr are not available). Please use the definitions given by equation 3.5.3a of Andrews, Holton and Leovy text book, but scaled by density to have units m3 s-2.
epfy.long_name: Northward Component of the Eliassen-Palm Flux

epfz.comment: Transformed Eulerian Mean Diagnostics Meridional component Fz of the Eliassen-Palm (EP) flux (Fy, Fz) derived from 6hr or higher frequency fields (use daily fields or 12 hr fields if the 6 hr are not available). Please use the definitions given by equation 3.5.3b of Andrews, Holton and Leovy text book, but scaled by density to have units m3 s-2.
epfz.long_name: Upward Component of the Eliassen-Palm Flux

es.comment: Water here means water in all phases. Evaporation is the conversion of liquid or solid into vapor. (The conversion of solid alone into vapor is called 'sublimation'.) In accordance with common usage in geophysical disciplines, 'flux' implies per unit area, called 'flux density' in physics.

esn.comment: Water here means water in all phases. Evaporation is the conversion of liquid or solid into vapor. (The conversion of solid alone into vapor is called 'sublimation'.) In accordance with common usage in geophysical disciplines, 'flux' implies per unit area, called 'flux density' in physics. Unless indicated in the cell_methods attribute, a quantity is assumed to apply to the whole area of each horizontal grid box. Previously, the qualifier where_type was used to specify that the quantity applies only to the part of the grid box of the named type.  Names containing the where_type qualifier are deprecated and newly created data should use the cell_methods attribute to indicate the horizontal area to which the quantity applies.

evs.comment: computed as the total mass of water vapor evaporating from the ice-free portion of the ocean  divided by the area of the ocean portion of the grid cell.
evs.long_name: Water Evaporation Flux Where Ice Free Ocean over Sea

evspsbl.comment: Evaporation at surface (also known as evapotranspiration): flux of water into the atmosphere due to conversion of both liquid and solid phases to vapor (from underlying surface and vegetation)

evspsblpot.comment: at surface; potential flux of water into the atmosphere due to conversion of both liquid and solid phases to vapor (from underlying surface and vegetation)

evspsblveg.comment: The canopy evaporation and sublimation (if present in model); may include dew formation as a negative flux.

evu.comment: Vertical diffusion coefficient for momentum due to parametrised eddies

expc.comment: Downward flux of particulate organic carbon
expc.long_name: Downward Flux of Particulate Organic Carbon

expfe.comment: In accordance with common usage in geophysical disciplines, 'flux' implies per unit area, called 'flux density' in physics.   'Sinking' is the gravitational settling of particulate matter suspended in a liquid. A sinking flux is positive downwards and is calculated relative to the movement of the surrounding fluid.
